T* (8\) Why FLOG_CHANNEL exists) Tj
T* (--------------------------) Tj
T* (FLOG_CHANNEL is very important for multi-client support.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Why:) Tj
T* (- Telegram file_id can vary per bot/client) Tj
T* (- this project may run multiple bots/sessions) Tj
T* (- each client may need its own valid file_id to access the same media) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (How it works:) Tj
T* (1. bot forwards or sends cached media to FLOG_CHANNEL) Tj
T* (2. every active client reads that same message from FLOG_CHANNEL) Tj
T* (3. project stores each client's file_id in DB under file_ids) Tj
T* (4. later the web streamer picks the best available client and uses that client's file_id) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (If FLOG_CHANNEL is not set:) Tj
T* (- the project falls back to simpler behavior) Tj
T* (- but multi-client support is weaker) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (9\) Multi-client mode) Tj
T* (--------------------) Tj
T* (Files:) Tj
T* (- FileStream/bot/__init__.py) Tj
T* (- FileStream/bot/clients.py) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (If environment contains MULTI_TOKEN1, MULTI_TOKEN2, etc.:) Tj
T* (- extra Pyrogram clients are started) Tj
T* (- primary bot handlers are cloned to them) Tj
T* (- each client is tracked in multi_clients) Tj
T* (- current load per client is tracked in work_loads) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Purpose:) Tj
T* (- distribute streaming load) Tj
T* (- reduce rate limit pressure) Tj
T* (- improve reliability for high traffic) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (During streaming, the project picks the client with the lowest current load.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (10\) How web streaming works) Tj
ET
endstream
