T* (Meaning:) Tj
T* (- /watch/{id}) Tj
T* (  returns HTML player page for one file) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- /dl/{id}) Tj
T* (  streams file bytes directly) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- /folder/{id}) Tj
T* (  returns HTML page listing files in a folder) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- /get-download-token/{id}) Tj
T* (  creates a one-time token for safer download) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (- /file/{token}) Tj
T* (  downloads/streams file using one-time token) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (11\) What happens when someone opens /dl/{id}) Tj
T* (--------------------------------------------) Tj
T* (Function:) Tj
T* (- media_streamer\(request, db_id\)) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Flow:) Tj
T* (1. choose the least loaded client) Tj
T* (2. create or reuse ByteStreamer for that client) Tj
T* (3. load file properties from DB) Tj
T* (4. decode Telegram file_id into Pyrogram FileId object) Tj
T* (5. support HTTP Range requests for streaming/seek) Tj
T* (6. open Telegram media session to correct data center) Tj
T* (7. fetch chunks from Telegram using raw upload.GetFile) Tj
T* (8. yield chunks to aiohttp response) Tj
T* (9. browser/player receives bytes like a normal file server) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (This is the core of the whole project.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Very important point:) Tj
T* (- the file is not first fully downloaded to your VPS) Tj
T* (- chunks are fetched from Telegram and passed through to the client) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (That is why the bot can stream large files without full server storage.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (12\) ByteStreamer internals) Tj
T* (--------------------------) Tj
T* (File:) Tj
T* (- FileStream/utils/custom_dl.py) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (ByteStreamer does these jobs:) Tj
T* (- cache file properties in memory) Tj
T* (- create media sessions for the correct Telegram DC) Tj
T* (- build file location objects) Tj
T* (- fetch media chunks from Telegram raw API) Tj
T* (- yield bytes piece by piece) Tj
T* (- update client workload counters while serving) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (It also periodically clears cache to reduce memory usage.) Tj
ET
endstream
