T* (- if domain/FQDN is wrong, links break) Tj
T* (- NSFW scan can be CPU-heavy) Tj
T* (- in-memory one-time download tokens are lost on restart) Tj
T* (- some features depend on bot having correct Telegram permissions) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (29\) Simple mental model) Tj
T* (-----------------------) Tj
T* (Think of the project as 3 layers:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Layer 1: Telegram bot layer) Tj
T* (- receives files) Tj
T* (- verifies users) Tj
T* (- stores metadata) Tj
T* (- sends buttons/links) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Layer 2: Database layer) Tj
T* (- remembers files, users, folders, settings, reports) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Layer 3: Web streaming layer) Tj
T* (- renders HTML pages) Tj
T* (- fetches Telegram chunks) Tj
T* (- streams bytes to browser) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (30\) Final summary) Tj
T* (-----------------) Tj
T* (FileStreamBot does NOT work like a normal upload server.) Tj
T* (It works like a bridge between Telegram and the web.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The bot saves file metadata in MongoDB.) Tj
T* (When someone opens a generated link, the aiohttp server fetches the file chunks from Telegram ) Tj
T* (through Pyrogram/raw API and streams them to the browser.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (That is the core design of the entire project.) Tj
ET
